The `additionalProperties` specify that every value in the map is an `object`, when really it can be any type (`int`, `string`, ect...). When we return a map that contains, for example, a `string`, this causes a validation failure in [bravado](https://github.com/Yelp/bravado). I think `interface{}` shouldn't have any `additionalProperties`.

