In order to generate the client API I've created a new EDN consumer and producer and can use the generated code to create a new client and send requests, however because the generated code lacks EDN struct tags, some of the struct fields are not populated when being unmarshaled.


I need to have additional tags added to the generated struct fields in order to use a custom producer/consumer.

Currently the generated code includes only JSON tags, and I've seen that I can use `x-go-custom-tag`, but that means I need to add the custom tag to each property manually?

Is there an easy way to add additional tag besides `json` to the generated models without having to touch the original Swagger spec?

I've also tried using a custom template which overrides `structfields`, but that doesn't work since this is a protected template.

