## Problem statement

When an API supports some form of caching, such as via [`Etag` headers](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/ETag), the generated client code makes it impossible to make full use of that caching today.

Of course the API consumer may still avoid performing some expensive operations with the data it has received. However, the `Etag` comes in the form of header, i.e. early enough that it could avoid downloading a single byte of the response body if the response has not changed since it was last seen. The stdlib `net/http` API also makes this possible as it does not download body until `Read()` is called on the [`http.Response`](https://pkg.go.dev/net/http#Response) `Body io.ReadCloser`.

The current design however implies that body is always downloaded and unmarshaled into the struct before the consumer had even the chance to compare `Etag`.

